This paper proposes a new neural network architecture for object recognition that integrates human knowledge and experience. The focus is on visual cognition, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of traditional neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the interpretability of neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the computational complexity of the proposed model, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
